I"º<p>In this survey of children and adults who follow a VLCD for the long-term treatment of T1DM, it was observed measures of glycemic control in the near-normal range, low rates of hypoglycemia and other adverse events, and generally high levels of satisfaction with health and diabetes control. These findings are without precedent among people with T1DM, revealing a novel approach to the prevention of long-term diabetes complications.</p>
